NS <b>GHOST</b>
-
Usage: /msg Nickserv <b>GHOST</b> <Nickname> <Password>
Usage: /ns <b>GHOST</b> <Nickname> <Password>
-
-
With <b>GHOST</b>, you can disconnect your client if you have become disconnected but your client is still online. 
Nickserv will then kill the connection of your ghost.  
-
- Example
- 
- NS <b>GHOST</b> foo myfoo123 
-
- <b>GHOST</b> - End of help
